    "status": "pass",
    "findings_fixed": [
      "Safe point does not mutate hart state or claim stop-the-world behavior; it only records quiesced semantic evidence",
      "Command preflight rejects stale participant generations and running harts",
      "Coordinator hart must be part of the participant set so coordinator evidence cannot float separately",
      "Every active hart must be present, preventing partial safe points from being reported as global evidence",
      "Hart event attribution avoids duplicate same-hart same-event records by using coordinator attribution as the coordinator participant evidence",
      "osctl ViewV1 and history graph edges expose typed hart id/generation references instead of raw debug labels"
    ],
